The Nigerian Equity Market resumed the trading week on a bearish note, recording a 0.03 per cent decline to halt last weekâ€™s bullish sentiment. Market breadth closed positive recording 20 gainers as against 17 losers. The All Share Index (ASI) declined 10.31 absolute points, representing a decrease of 0.03 per cent to close at 30,076.00 points. Conversely, Market Capitalization increased by N2.42 billion representing a growth of 0.02 per cent to close at N11.30 trillion as result of SAHCO listing on the Mainboard of the Nigerian Stock Exchange. JAPAULOIL emerged the top gainer while GUINNESS emerged as the top loser. The downturn was impacted by losses recorded in medium and large capitalized stocks, amongst which are; FO (-9.83%), UNILEVER (-8.82%), AFRIPRUD (-3.50%), GUARANTY (-2.01%), TRANSCORP (-1.68%), NB (-1.54%), FLOURMILL (-0.61%), and WAPCO (-0.43%). (GTI)